Exposure of cerebellar granule cells, endogenously expressing A1R, to 100 nM R-PIA for 2–48 h led to a blunting of the inhibition of adenylyl cyclase. Along with this observation, a decrease of [3H]cyclohexyladenosine ([3H]CHA) binding to intact cerebellar granule cells and an increase of [3H]CHA binding in microsomes was detected. Simultaneously, a decrease in the steady-state level of \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
