\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
\begin{document}$${\text{G}}_{{{\text{i}}\alpha }} $$\end{document} in plasma membrane and microsomes was observed. These findings point not only to homologous desensitization, but also to subsequent internalization of the A1R in the microsomal fraction of cerebellar granule cells upon long-term agonist exposure. However, no change in mRNA level was observed, suggesting that post-transcriptional regulation underlies receptor desensitization [39].

